Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper proposes a model that emulates saccades, which are rapid eye movements used for visual perception. The model is based on the Predictive Vision Model (PVM), which is a computer vision model. 
2. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The Error Saccade Model is based on the prediction error of the PVM, which is a neural network model. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a model that uses machine learning techniques to emulate saccades and improve visual perception. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The Error Saccade Model is a machine learning model that learns to move the field of view to regions with the highest prediction error. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper discusses the ability of the Error Saccade Model to pursue detailed objects in its view, which is relevant to robotics applications that require visual perception.
